reccomplex.configgui.title: Structure Gen Config
reccomplex.structure.metadata.tooltip:
Text data describing the structure,
like the author or a comment.
reccomplex.structure.generation.tooltip: How the structure generates in the world.
reccomplex.structure.transformers.toolti:
Scripts that alter generation of
the structure randomly.
reccomplex.structure.dependencies.toolti:
If not matched, the structure won't generate.
It is not technically required to
use this, but it will help
with modded structures.
reccomplex.structure.orientation.tooltip:
Whether the structure can be rotated or mirrored.
These may need to be set to false
when using specific TileEntities or Entities.
reccomplex.structure.blocking.tooltip:
Whether the structure stops other structures
from spawning in the same place.
reccomplex.structure.variables.tooltip:
Toggles specific to the structure
that can be used in environment
expressions everywhere within the
structure.
reccomplex.structure.variables.id.toolti:
Unique Identifier of the toggle
(what is used in the expressions)
reccomplex.structure.variables.chance.to: Chance for the toggle to trigger (-> true)
reccomplex.structure.variables.logical.t:
True if the toggle affects placement logic
(e.g. maze exits).
False if it's purely visual.
reccomplex.structure.deleteOther.tooltip:
Note: Structures in the %s
folder take loading precedence
over those in the %s folder.
reccomplex.structure.generation.id.toolt:
Identifier for the generation type.
Unique within the structure file.
reccomplex.generationInfo.natural.limita:
Structure occurs x times at max,
per dimension.
Rooms that this component spans over.
Keep in mind these are scaled by
the maze's room size.

Exits leading outside of this component.
Keep in mind these are scaled by
the maze's room size.

East/West Position of this exit.
Keep in mind this is scaled by
the maze's room size.

Up/Down Position of this exit.
Keep in mind this is scaled by
the maze's room size.

South/North Position of this exit.
Keep in mind this is scaled by
the maze's room size.
reccomplex.generationInfo.static.tooltip:
Constant Position in a specific dimension
Also useful for spawn structures.
reccomplex.generationInfo.static.pattern:
Number of blocks after which
the structure is generated again.

Random displacement for each
placement of the structure.
As part of a structure list
(Used in structure blocks)
reccomplex.generationInfo.vanilla.toolti:
As part of a vanilla structure
(Like villages)
reccomplex.generationInfo.vanilla.title: In Complex Structure
reccomplex.generationInfo.vanilla.amount:
Amount of this structure in
every village.

Amount of this structure in
every village, scaled by the village size.
reccomplex.generationInfo.sapling.toolti: As a tree from a sapling.
reccomplex.generationInfo.sapling.title: Sapling
reccomplex.generationInfo.decoration.too:
Instead of a vanilla decoration entry
(e.g. trees, mushrooms, cacti).
reccomplex.generationInfo.decoration.typ:
An ocean monument with guardians,
sea lanterns and prismarine.

Various scattered features
such as witch huts.
Villages filled with villagers and farms.

Fortresses in the Nether filled with blazes
made from nether brick.
A stronghold containing the end portal.
Mineshafts in the ground filled with random loot.
reccomplex.transformer.block.source.tool:
Blocks in the structure that this
transformer applies to.
reccomplex.transformer.block.dest.toolti:
Blocks in the environment that this
transformer runs over.
reccomplex.transformer.worldscript.toolt: Runs a world script from matched blocks.
reccomplex.transformer.villagereplace.to:
Replaces all applicable blocks
to the version native to
the village.
reccomplex.transformer.natural.tooltip: Spawns biome-native floor blocks below blocks
reccomplex.transformer.natural.naturalEx: The amount of randomization in the distance.
reccomplex.transformer.naturalAir.natura: The amount of randomization in the distance.
reccomplex.transformer.pillar.tooltip: Constructs pillars down to the floor
reccomplex.transformer.replace.uniformit:
Whether all blocks should be
replaced by the same block.
reccomplex.transformer.ruins.decay.title: 腐朽
The amount of blocks that will
be deleted when the structure generates.
reccomplex.transformer.ruins.decay.chaos:
The level at which the structure's
decay may differ within the
same structure.
reccomplex.transformer.ruins.decay.densi:
The density of different decay progressions.
In short, set this low for big holes
and high for small holes.
reccomplex.transformer.ruins.decay.direc: The direction the decay happens towards.
reccomplex.transformer.ruins.other.title: 其他
reccomplex.transformer.ruins.erosion.too:
The chance for each block
to be replaced by a
'broken' version of it.
reccomplex.transformer.ruins.vines.toolt:
The chance for vines and moss
to spawn on each block.
reccomplex.transformer.ruins.cobwebs.too: The chance for cobwebs to form in corners.
reccomplex.transformer.ruins.gravity.too:
Blocks that are floating
fall down at generation.
reccomplex.transformer.ensureBlocks.tool:
Cancels the generation if
any placed blocks don't have space.
reccomplex.transformer.propertyReplace.t:
Searches the block states for specific
properties and replaces them with
the given values.

reccomplex.expression.positioned_block.t:

reccomplex.expression.dependency.tooltip:

reccomplex.expression.environment.toolti:

reccomplex.maze.connector.tooltip:
The ID of the connector.
These work like electronical connectors.

§bHermaphrodite§r (default): Connects to itself.

If the ID starts with...
§bMale:§r Connects to female counterpart.
§bFemale:§r Connects to male counterpart.
reccomplex.maze.conditional_connectors.t:
Connectors that will be used
if certain conditions are met.
reccomplex.reachability.tooltip:
Describes reachability between
the exits of this maze component.
reccomplex.reachability.groups.tooltip:
All paths in one group
are reachable between
each other.
reccomplex.mazerule.connect.tooltip: Ensure a path between two exits.
reccomplex.mazerule.connectall.tooltip: Ensure a path between all exits.
reccomplex.mazerule.connect.start.toolti:
Connect any of these to
any of the end paths.
reccomplex.mazerule.connect.end.tooltip:
Connect any of these to
any of the start paths.
reccomplex.worldscript.mazeGen.tooltip: Generates a maze from weighted components.
reccomplex.worldscript.strucGen.tooltip: Generates a structure from weighted options.
reccomplex.worldscript.holder.tooltip:
A script holding an area
that will generate from the
script on structure generation.
For complex use-cases, use
list generation instead.
reccomplex.worldscript.holder.holder.too: Switches an area of blocks between two setups.
reccomplex.worldscript.holder.point.1.to: The first point of the area.
reccomplex.worldscript.holder.point.2.to: The second point of the area.
reccomplex.worldscript.holder.self.toolt:
The block placed at the position
of this script.
reccomplex.gui.random.weight.custom.shor:
C reccomplex.gui.random.weight.tooltip=Weight of this element for random selection.
§achance = weight / sum_of_all_weights§r
In other words, twice the weight means
twice as likely.
Set to D for the default value.
reccomplex.preset.title:
Title
reccomplex.preset.title.tooltip=Title=Visible title of the preset
reccomplex.preset.description.tooltip:
Visible description for the preset.
Use
to start a new line.
The unique ID of this component.
reccomplex.gui.inventorygen.groupid.tool:
The shared group ID of this component.
All components using this ID
will be added to the loot
table with this name.
reccomplex.inventorygen.dependencies.too:
If not matched, the loot table won't activate.
It is not technically required to
use this, but it will help
with modded structures.
reccomplex.gui.blockpos.tooltip: The coordinates x, y and z.
reccomplex.gui.blockpos.shift.tooltip: The positional movement x, y, z.
reccomplex.placer.baseline.tooltip:
The height of the surface in the structure.
'0' would mean the first row of
blocks are at surface height.
reccomplex.placer.factor.priority.toolti:
Priority that this factor
will be considered at.
This value is fed into a pow scale:
weight ^ priority
reccomplex.placer.factors.limit.tooltip:
Limit placement to specific heights.
Casts rays that set the acceptance for the
terrain they pass by until they hit.
reccomplex.placer.factors.limit.ray.weig:
Acceptance reccomplex.placer.factors.limit.ray.weight.tooltip=The ratio to which this area is accepted.
(eg. 0 = don't spawn here, 1 = do spawn here).
Set to ignore to just move
without changing acceptance.
reccomplex.placer.factors.limit.rays.mov: Move up or down a specified distance
reccomplex.placer.factors.limit.rays.dyn:
Top (World Height) reccomplex.placer.factors.limit.rays.dynpos.type.world_height.tooltip=Top of the world:
y = 255 - structure_height
Move a dynamic amount of blocks
The height of the spawning structure
reccomplex.placer.factors.limit.rays.mat:
Move until the terrain fulfills
the set criteria.

The ratio of matched blocks
required until the ray stops.
reccomplex.placer.factors.limit.rays.ave:
Find the average surface height
fulfilling the criteria.
reccomplex.placer.factors.match.tooltip:
Ensure specific blocks from the
structure to have fitting
terrain to spawn in.
reccomplex.placer.factors.match.conformi:
How much conformity to the match
is required to allow the structure
to spawn.
reccomplex.blockpattern.pattern.tooltip:
The pattern / shape of blocks
required to spawn.
reccomplex.blockpattern.ingredients.tool:
Information about the blocks used
in the pattern.
